{"TopicId":217818,"ForumId":144,"TopicTitle":"Camera resets position every time you enter and exit map view","CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-22T16:41:15Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-22T16:41:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.4 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i7-8700 | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Geforce 1070Ti | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs per the title, anytime you enter and exit the map view the flight camera gets reset back to its original position, rather than keeping the position before entering map view.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAnth Edit: Adding More Information:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EObserved Behavior:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe Flight View camera angle is changing on returning from Map View, and is regularly ending up in the middle of the craft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EExpected Behavior:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nWhen going from Flight View to Map View and than back again, the Flight View camera angle and distance should be\u003Cstrong\u003E identical\u003C/strong\u003E to what it was before.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003ESteps to Replicate:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Col\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nLoad \u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=EveOrbitCameraTestSave.json\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5BhBu9ZbGXThJShZJlFF/4H2Ohf8Sewgo6WpGaH3lGoeZZdOG/xRMao/KTyICd/IuovRsAeSTd9cd72XD%2BwLGFs1j9JSbAgqelNahL8g==%5D%5B16eab68010b8429a24c16995%5D%5Bfc5de2c2e4a940e48ea9031723f386c6%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EEveOrbitCameraTestSave.json\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nNote position\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nPress M twice\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nNote change in position\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nPress M twice\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nNote camera is now in the middle of the craft\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EVideo Evidence:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/q89Vot94fn8\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://youtu.be/q89Vot94fn8\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0(11 Seconds)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#c0392b;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:20px;\u0022\u003EResult:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe player has to regularly zoom out again and again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-10-17T19:09:20Z\u0022 title=\u002210/17/2023 07:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Oct 17\u0022\u003EOctober 17, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-20T17:10:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is still an issue in 0.2, and the camera is even worse or I just noticed its other defects now that I am actually trying to play it.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe other issues with the camera are as follows:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1) Impossible to get an \u0022orbital\u0022 camera view (ie the same camera view as the map) when in space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2) All the current camera views (other than chase) do the exact same thing for some reason when in orbit/space.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3) Switching between flight and map view always resets the camera back to a different camera view than I one I picked. For example, if you use \u0022chase\u0022 mode and switch to map and back, it is no longer in chase mode.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4) Dragging the camera with right mouse is too slow and there is no way to change it without changing mouse sensitivity (which impacts the cursor as well).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RalphKerman","CreatedById":229516,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-22T18:08:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost simple way to reproduce:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBuild any vessel, go to launchpad, press M for Map and M again -\u0026gt; you camera is 180 degrees off from where it started in the middle of\u00A0 the launch tower.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWin 10, Steam install, version 0.1.3 (released 2023-06-22), no mods installed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-22T17:43:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan confirm.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBefore switching to map:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022HoSclo5.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/HoSclo5.jpg\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ReOWLko.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/ReOWLko.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n(far away and the opposite direction)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RalphKerman","CreatedById":229516,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T20:52:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217818\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693423245\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184845\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MechBFP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, MechBFP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is partially fixed in 1.4. It keeps the same general direction you were looking, which is better, but it does not maintain the \u003Cstrong\u003Eexact \u003C/strong\u003Ecamera position.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, it does no longer flip around 180 degrees but it resets the translation values to 0 every time you return from map view. So you are looking at your craft exactly from the default position and any camera translation you did before entering map view is reset. Not as annoying as the original bug but very disappointing that this slipped through considering how often you go to the map view and back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-02T13:10:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224318660\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217818\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693649711\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219348\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vl3d\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Vl3d said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis seems OK for me in 0.1.4 - when toggling map view, the camera defaults to a sensible default zoom centered on the vessel. Is not restoring the exact zoom level / camera orientation when toggling M really a bug that should inherit the previous 30 upvotes?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NaughtyMonster","CreatedById":210559,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-02T21:29:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis still seems to be an issue (even in 0.1.4).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBefore going to map view:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Before-map.png?rlkey=wnhcx26w9pt1cpl7oof\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/rrngz8cvifadru37khbyo/Before-map.png?rlkey=wnhcx26w9pt1cpl7oofysqq7f\u0026amp;dl=1\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn returning from map view (view is now from inside the large hydrogen tank):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022After-map.png?rlkey=xnyenf2rm01ys7gupsf5\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/m106489oqqcncvkwjhzkw/After-map.png?rlkey=xnyenf2rm01ys7gupsf51gc2u\u0026amp;dl=1\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter rotating view 90 degrees down:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022After-map-2.png?rlkey=0k3ng7sy94mlop8nyn\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/78f9kcaeuubtj2mmxz0lw/After-map-2.png?rlkey=0k3ng7sy94mlop8nyn3o4a1xc\u0026amp;dl=1\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-09-02T21:38:09Z\u0022 title=\u002209/02/2023 09:38  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Sep 2\u0022\u003ESeptember 2, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by NaughtyMonster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Abelinoss","CreatedById":222638,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-06T19:19:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.4 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 5 5600 6-core Processor | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0NVIDEA GeForce RTX 3060 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E15.91GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn patch 4 it seems like quicksave-quickload now works properly with remaining camera positions, but going to map view and back still resets the camera.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot hard to reproduce as it happens literally every time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=KerbalSpaceProgram22023-09-0620-29-59.mp4\u0026amp;fileKey=%5B!AES128GCM%5BQ3Qun9lzJS28ygchVBo0ciKqBYWcE3xvNuFq7kfESNdqnrjHVnUYAE/f2PKsSqQugDaFAJYkxfeOSBikEACzN6A5faVV35F7oNqKcpBY2CTO3uL1azkU5urHZKEG8g==%5D%5Bbfe0dddc893c8b3ebb96e3f9%5D%5B393e7a5ed2387b0fa886102d3812cc7f%5D%5D\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003EKerbalSpaceProgram22023-09-0620-29-59.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-09-06T22:15:19Z\u0022 title=\u002209/06/2023 10:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Sep 6\u0022\u003ESeptember 6, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Anth12\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-27T21:50:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/231845-bc2307/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022231845\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/231845-bc2307/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@bc2307\u003C/a\u003E, merged your bug report.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sade","CreatedById":226252,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-20T14:00:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0W11 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A05600X | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A07900XTX | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32Gb\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIssue:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSwitching from the map view to the flight view and back resets the map view camera position. This is made even more annoying because it is zoomed completely in. This causes excessive mouse wheel scrolling to zoom back out to see the maneuver node.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Abelinoss","CreatedById":222638,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-07-29T07:10:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI want to add that this also happens when doing quicksave/quickload\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-08-30T19:20:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is partially fixed in 1.4. It keeps the same general direction you were looking, which is better, but it does not maintain the \u003Cstrong\u003Eexact \u003C/strong\u003Ecamera position.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-02T10:15:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224317458\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217818\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221693423245\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184845\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MechBFP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/30/2023 at 10:20 PM, MechBFP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is partially fixed in 1.4. It keeps the same general direction you were looking, which is better, but it does not maintain the \u003Cstrong\u003Eexact \u003C/strong\u003Ecamera position.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis seems OK for me in 0.1.4 - when toggling map view, the camera defaults to a sensible default zoom centered on the vessel. Is not restoring the exact zoom level / camera orientation when toggling M really a bug that should inherit the previous 30 upvotes?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-09-15T22:36:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/222638-abelinoss/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022222638\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/222638-abelinoss/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Abelinoss\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0Merged with this one.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Anth","CreatedById":161238,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-17T19:10:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/184845-mechbfp/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022184845\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/184845-mechbfp/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@MechBFP\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nAdded my bug report after yours within your original post.\u003Cbr\u003E\nMoving my duplicate to the archive.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-25T21:50:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill in 0.1.5\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RalphKerman","CreatedById":229516,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-27T12:17:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI do not get this bug anymore in 0.1.5\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTried a simple craft and launched it, I zoomed a little out and turned the camera about 30 degrees in each direction so I looked from a little above the vehicle down to the surface. I entered the map multiple times and switched back (always using keyboard \u0022M\u0022) and also did stuff on the map like rotating, creating a node etc. When I switched back to the vehicle the camera was exactly where it was before I entered the map mode.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo in this scenario it appears to be fixed completely but I read in the K.E.R.B. topic that they wrote that some refactoring is needed to fix it fully.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PicoSpace","CreatedById":224964,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-30T14:28:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.5 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Win10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A05800X | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A03070 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E64\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nQuite Annoying 99% of the time going from map view to vessel for it to start zoomed in on the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E of the rocket such that its \u0022black or mostly black\u0022 and then you have to scroll the camera out.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSometimes depending on center of mass you get a cool shot like this... but the rest of the time its annoying.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis mainly occures in Kerbol (the star) \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E space when travelling interplanetary, the alternative is\u00A0\u00A0\u0022quirk\u0022 is the camera will reset itself to an odd angle where its pointing straight up or down in Kerbol \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E space.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt would be nice if the direction of view was either persistant between the two views or matched the camera angles.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/uploads/monthly_2023_10/20231029225053_1.jpg.cda49ffa74968896f7f45c386c5784ae.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ipslightbox=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-10-30T14:37:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/224964-picospace/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022224964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/224964-picospace/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@PicoSpace\u003C/a\u003E, merged your bug report.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mattihase","CreatedById":73161,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-24T15:30:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.1.5 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 10 | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i7-10870H | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0RTX 3070 | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E16GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nno idea what\u0027s triggered it but whenever I return from map view I find myself staring out from the centre of my vessel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-24T21:04:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/73161-mattihase/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002273161\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/73161-mattihase/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@mattihase\u003C/a\u003E, merged your bug report.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Unfawkable","CreatedById":93524,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T17:23:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 Pro 64-bit (10.0, Build 22621) (22621.ni_release.220506-1250) | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Ryzen 5 5600 6-Core Processor (12 CPUs), ~3.5GHz | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0AMD Radeon RX 6750 XT | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32768MB RAM\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETitle:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003EUpon opening the map with the M hotkey, and closing it to return to the craft, the camera is fully zoomed in every time I do this.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESeverity:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0Low, you can just Zoom out, just annoying\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFrequency:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003ELow, first time it happened.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022background-color:#f9f9f9;color:#2d3134;font-size:15px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:16px;\u0022\u003EDescription:\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0 U\u003C/strong\u003Ensure how to reproduce, it started happening after I saved the game right after lifting off from the Mun and making a low Mun Orbit. Then I saved and quit there. After loading later that day, this behavior started.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=ZoomBug.mkv\u0026amp;fileKey=[!AES128GCM[3G4W2rcB5mMBJr76cwnieDnPq6JrpMFfUc0/gJworkRTcrf7y1FeJyDtzdP6tcNJDG8pvvJoMI8/sHC3][1e59123dd9ff7dbf4c545da9][9a72e294b9e53bcfabf8feba1646627a]]\u0022\u003EZoomBug.mkv\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-22T19:05:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/93524-unfawkable/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002293524\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/93524-unfawkable/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Unfawkable\u003C/a\u003E, merged your bug report.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bc2307","CreatedById":231845,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-12-27T18:36:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EReported Version:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0v0.2.0 (latest) |\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003EMods:\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Enone | \u003Cstrong\u003ECan replicate without mods?\u003C/strong\u003E Yes\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EOS:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0Windows 11 Pro | \u003Cstrong\u003ECPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0i9-11900K | \u003Cstrong\u003EGPU:\u003C/strong\u003E\u00A0GeForce RTX 4070 Ti | \u003Cstrong\u003ERAM\u003Cspan\u003E:\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E32 GB\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen switching between the map screen and vessel, the camera starts inside the vessel. This has only occured to me with this vessel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EIncluded Attachments:\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=Caminsidevessel.mp4\u0026amp;fileKey=[!AES128GCM[iIye1paGF%2BlaXvVKrbOAg9WvFYdPaU5LORFKttXrG3OQ3T5rv4TRMYdy3/IlAaSgacBE1974Lkw0qT%2BQ1O4%2BeXlxzBtevXZV][e6cbec0a2de70d3e5c6c4565][bf76be75b5207002f61e4b6e8d65a520]]\u0022\u003ECaminsidevessel.mp4\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/applications/core/interface/file/cfield.php?storage=form_Fields\u0026amp;path=quicksave_44.json\u0026amp;fileKey=[!AES128GCM[DEWrR0k%2BX2Xs77CQ2zvR3HTBg/i66/C6/LQVDDG4/NK0TApbkoS5W0RhnKE4lJFdaHZvYpLVJRSSGo4AQFGH4L8n][1c6cc9c0a98268096894462a][033ed9ea58e0352a20e889c0d1ff65d5]]\u0022\u003Equicksave_44.json\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cstyle type=\u0022text/css\u0022\u003E\r\n.ipsImage {\r\nwidth: 900px !important;\r\n}\u003C/style\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-01-20T16:49:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/226252-sade/?do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022226252\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/profile/226252-sade/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Sade\u003C/a\u003E, merged your bug report.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}